annotations: It was just a ghost that sorta looked just like you

Another reference to another track on the record, this time “all of my ghosts”:

All my ghosts are with me

I’ve been hosting screenings
 Of slightly altered movie scenes
 Seems familiar ’til I realize that they look just like me

This is a clear reference to the next track on the album, “ceilings”:

You kiss me in your car
And it feels like the start of a movie I’ve seen before

I’ve been having strange dreams
 Seeing ghosts and breaking things

“Seeing ghosts” likely refers to the meaning of track 5, “all my ghosts”. In that song, Lizzy sings about the baggage that comes with her past experiences and relationships, as she enters a new one.

In the context of “weird”, this line could mean that she is seeing her old relationships and regrets in her dreams.

search_results.title: Grass Stains
search_results.lyrics:
Grass Stains LyricsSaw some old friends in my dreams and
They're just as I remember, singin' songs in houses built too tall
The walls were painted red, your name was etched into the armchair
You said it'd last forever but we never seemed to get there

And I heard you cry and I sighed
I felt enough for the both of us

I see bluebirds fly so high, so high
And yet I've still got two feet stuck in the ground
Is life holdin' me down or am I just around?
Through the worst of it
Summer songs were sung in circles, we'd passed around
The cheapest brews and laughed until the sky turned blue
I'd watch the sparks fly from the fire and learned to form a metaphor
For all the things I felt for you and all the things you wouldn't do

And I heard you cry and I sighed
I felt enough for the both of us

I see bluebirds fly so high, so high
And yet I've still got two feet stuck in the ground
Is life holdin' me down or am I just around?
Through the worst of it

Grass stains, on my knees, I fall down
Old, old friends are nowhere to be found, woah

I see bluebirds fly so high, so high
And yet I've still got two feet stuck in the ground
Is life holdin' me down or am I just around?
Through the worst of it
Through the worst of itYou might also like2Embed
